> Thanks for the quick fix. Just want to double confirm the change can work well on both Py2 and Py3 as we have both Py2 and Py3.

Yes, it should work. The current setup and the different scenarios that leads to choosing Python interpreter are -

- Ansible invoking Python on PTF uses default interpreter "/usr/bin/python". On mixed image (py2+py3) it will choose Python 2. When/after migrating to the py3only (currently piloting) image "/usr/bin/python" will automatically invoke Python 3 interpreter.
- When tests call ptf_runner.py the `ptf_runner` function detects the type of PTF container, the script and automatically choose the right interpreter.
- For test scripts that have been migrated to Python 3 and files under `ansible/roles/test/files/py3` and other related files the link resolves to `/root/env-python3/bin/python3` or `/root/env-python3/bin/ptf` and they are set to Python 3 on both mixed and py3only images.

#15772 - Uses the single conditional
#16118 - Switches back to double-conditional
#16535 - (this PR) fixes "==" issue with 15772
TBD PR - Adds cisco back to the other condition.

 PFC_STORM...

 pytest_assert...
